Java 8 features: To promote Functional programming.

i)Lambda Expression
ii)Functional Interface
iii)Method References
iv)Stream API
v)Optional class
vi)Collection class
vii)Date ans Time API


Lambda Expression:A lambda expression is a function without a name.

syntax: (parameter list) -> body(expression/code)

() -> System.out.print("No parameters");

s -> System.out.print(s);

(int x, int y) -> x+y;

Advantages:
i)Conciseness
ii)Functional Programming
iii)Improved readability
iV)Flexibility




Functional Interface:
i)Interface with single abstract method.
ii)It can have any number of static, default method.
iii)Functional interface annotated with @FunctionalInterface

example: Runnable, Callable, Camparator, ActionLister

Method References:
It is used to refer method of the functional interface.
It is a compact and easy form of lambda expression.


4 types of method references:
i)Reference to a static method
ii)Reference to an instance method of a particular object.
iii)Reference to an instance method of an arbitrary object of a particular type.
iv)Reference to a constructor.

























